  <body>
    <section xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0"
             xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" name="MissingOverrideOnRecordAccessor">
      <p>Since Checkstyle 12.4.0</p>
      <subsection name="Description" id="MissingOverrideOnRecordAccessor_Description">
        <div>
          Verifies that explicitly declared record accessor methods include
          the <code>@Override</code> annotation.
        </div>

        <p>
          Per <a href="https://openjdk.org/jeps/395">JEP 395</a>, the meaning of the
          <code>@Override</code> annotation was extended to include explicitly declared
          accessor methods for record components.
        </p>

        <p>
          This check focuses only on record component accessor methods. It does not
          attempt to detect general method overrides from interfaces or superclasses,
          due to Checkstyle's single-file analysis limitations.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Examples" id="MissingOverrideOnRecordAccessor_Examples">
        <p id="Example1-config"> To configure the check:</p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="MissingOverrideOnRecordAccessor"/&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example1-code">Example:</p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
record Person(String name, int age) {

  // violation below, 'method must include @java.lang.Override annotation.'
  public String name() {
    return name.toUpperCase();
  }

  @Override
  public int age() {
    return age;
  }
}
</code></pre></div>
        <hr class="example-separator"/>
        <p id="Example2-config"> To configure the check:</p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-xml">
&lt;module name="Checker"&gt;
  &lt;module name="TreeWalker"&gt;
    &lt;module name="MissingOverrideOnRecordAccessor"/&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
</code></pre></div>
        <p id="Example2-code">Example with record implementing interface
            (only record component accessors flagged):</p>
        <div class="wrapper"><pre class="prettyprint"><code class="language-java">
interface Printable {
  void print();
}

record Document(String title) implements Printable {

  // violation below 'method must include @java.lang.Override annotation.'
  public String title() {
    return title.toUpperCase();
  }

  public void print() {
    System.out.println(title);
  }
}
</code></pre></div>
      </subsection>
